OL,6,FThe court was told that the daughter
OL,7,Fwho contacted police on July 17
OL,8,Fnormally lives in Brussels and that
OL,9,Fshe last spoke to her father on July 1.
OL,11,FThe judge was told she had difficulty
OL,12,Faccessing the home on previous
OL,13,Foccasions and had been in touch with
OL,14,Fpolice raising concerns about her
OL,15,Ffather.
OL,17,FPolice subsequently sent safeguarding
OL,18,Freferrals to social services in regard
OL,19,Fto the living conditions and the
OL,20,Fability of Noel O'Sullivan to look
OL,21,Fafter himself.
